						<summary>

						<p>Hero-stone (No. 9) set up in a field to the west of the village.</p>						

						<p>964-65 A.D.</p>						

						<p>The record is dated Śaka 886 corresponding to 964-65 A.D. It registers a gift of land by the king and the <hi rend="italic">ūru</hi> in memory of a hero (name lost) who died during a cattle-raid at Maṅgala. It states that Vajjaḻadēva was ruling over Puli-nāḍu.</p>						

						</summary>
